class Solution {
public:
    string reverseWords(string s) {
        string res = "";
        string word = "";
        for (char c : s) {
            if (c == ' ') {
                res += word;
                res += ' ';
                word = "";
            } else {
                word = c + word;
            }
        }
        res += word;
        return res;
    }
};
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution iterates through the input string once, reversing each word in place and appending it to the result string. It achieves high efficiency by minimizing the number of operations and avoiding unnecessary memory allocations.

